name: Hotel Shagun

reviews.review_text:
Having eaten here before when the restaurant first opened and having been a regular visitor one-two times every year, it is sad to see how far the restaurant has declined.

As I entered the restaurant, the smell of decaying meat welcomed me. Staff were not bothered to give you a menu or take the order. Most of the time they were just lounging around.

The food was average. Chicken Schezuan was not cooked, just chunks dipped in gravy and served. It smelled bad too. While eating, a cockroach fell from the ceiling into the chicken dish and saved me the trouble of finishing the dish. I called out to the waiters to take the cockroach away and they're just watching the cockroach struggling to get out of the gravy. The cleaner boy was atleast responsive and took the dish away. I did not even bother to ask for a replacement dish.

There is a lot of improvement needed in many areas of this restaurant. If the waiters and staff seem least bothered about their own restaurant, then you should also not bother.

One of the best places to have your favourite biryani in Goa. I just love their mutton biryani and malai tandoori which is the best I have ever had that no other places ever offered such a fantastic delicious food. I had my pre-wedding food catered from them. Definitely offers quality food and assures quality. Thank you so much for delivering superb food.

I recently had the pleasure of enjoying the chicken biryani at Hotel Shagun, and it was absolutely delightful! The biryani was perfectly balanced – not too spicy but with just the right amount of masala to give it a rich and flavorful taste. The spices were well blended, enhancing the overall experience without overwhelming the palate. The quality of the chicken was excellent, tender, and cooked to perfection. If you’re looking for a biryani that’s flavorful yet gentle, I highly recommend Hotel Shagun. A must-try for biryani lovers!

description:
### Hotel Shagun: A Culinary Journey in Aquem

Nestled in the vibrant locale of Aquem, Hotel Shagun boasts a commendable rating of **4.1** out of **871 reviews**, positioning it as a notable option for both locals and visitors alike. Customers often highlight tags such as **“price”**, **“mutton biryani”**, **“halal”**, and **“non-veg”**, indicating a focus on affordability and rich South Asian culinary traditions.

### Ambiance & Design

As you step into Hotel Shagun, you are greeted by an ambiance that hints at traditional Indian dining, characterized by a simple yet inviting décor. The lighting, warm and welcoming, aims to create a relaxed environment for revelers. However, some reviews suggest that experience can vary drastically, with recent comments highlighting concerns over cleanliness and overall maintenance. Attention to the aesthetic details seems to be a point for improvement, as one review noted an unsettling encounter with pests that marred the dining experience, overshadowing the otherwise promising atmosphere.

### Menu & Culinary Experience

The heart of Hotel Shagun lies within its kitchen, particularly praised for its **mutton biryani**—deemed “the best in Goa” by some enthusiasts. It's not just the mutton biryani that garners accolades; the **malai tandoori** also receives glowing reviews for its exquisite taste. One patron shared their experience with the **chicken biryani**, emphasizing its perfect blend of spices and tender chicken that delights without overwhelming. However, this sentiment stands starkly against claims of subpar dishes, such as the **Chicken Schezuan**, which was described as poorly executed and improperly cooked in one customer's unfortunate experience.

Additionally, the restaurant is noted for offering **halal** options, making it a go-to for those seeking compliant dining experiences. With dishes aesthetically presented, supported by enticing images showcasing vibrant colors and textures, the culinary artistry at Hotel Shagun is apparent, although not without room for consistency across dishes.

### Customer Experience & Service

Service at Hotel Shagun appears to be a mixed bag according to customer feedback. While some patrons laud the quality of food and express satisfaction with catering services for personal events, others report dismal experiences concerning staff attentiveness. Comments on service highlight instances where waitstaff seemed disengaged, which unfortunately can compromise the overall dining experience. For those interested in visiting, it may be wise to inquire about **reservation or walk-in policies**, as busy periods could significantly affect both food preparation and service times.

### Popularity & Reviews

The sentiment surrounding Hotel Shagun is reflected in the diverse reviews that paint a picture of both faithful patrons and disappointed diners. The restaurant's ability to swing from culinary excellence—especially regarding its biryani offerings—to distressing lapses in hygiene and service creates a complex narrative in the local dining scene. Despite recent criticisms, the commitment to delivering quality food has prompted returning guests, some even entrusting their pre-wedding events to the restaurant's catering services. 

Across platforms, the restaurant appears engaged with its community, inviting discussion and feedback that addresses both its high and low points, showcasing its resilience and potential for improvement.

### Utilizing Visual Content

The images shared by patrons evoke a sense of vibrant culinary appeal—whether it’s showcasing a sumptuous biryani or the allure of their grilled tandoori dishes. With visuals that highlight the colorful presentation of food, as seen in [this photo](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/geougc-cs/AHRlGdnadz2bUyw8PlEuokJL8Yo-iTmdmxiAqZOXcVxN8mKx7QVvC95ZJHBWyloFUJQY4VQLfD0RmRxEvhYpv2xbOVoMK6iKHKOGAykiiXZLqDaBOXMhctzBVP9hT4ApPOqXMavZC2FciQ=w375-h281-p), it’s clear that while experiences may differ, the potential for enjoyment at Hotel Shagun is not to be overlooked.

### Conclusion

In essence, Hotel Shagun stands as a culinary establishment beckoning biryani lovers and those seeking a halal dining experience. While the potential for a delightful meal exists, the restaurant must address service dynamics and cleanliness to truly shine in the competitive dining landscape of Goa. A cautious approach may be warranted; however, for fans of authentic biryani, a visit might just be worth the gamble.
